&lt;div class="post-text" itemprop="text"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;Select&lt;/code&gt; statement &lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;is&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; the reason to introduce concurrency at language syntax level in Go. Concurrent function call can (and usually done) be implemented on library level  with helper function like &lt;code&gt;spawn( function())&lt;/code&gt; and channels just as data structures with mutex or lock in most other languages. But &lt;code&gt;select&lt;/code&gt; statement can't.&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;

