&lt;p&gt;The trick is that there isn't just one cart, there are multiple carts. One being filled, one being moved to the incinerator, on being emptied into the incinerator, and one being moved back from the incinerator. This means that each gopher should (as long as things are working reasonably and the completion time of each task is relatively similar) always be busy.&lt;/p&gt;
