&lt;div class="post-text" itemprop="text"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;IMAP is a &lt;a href="http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc3501" rel="nofollow"&gt;simple textual protocol&lt;/a&gt; which is &lt;em&gt;very&lt;/em&gt; similar to &lt;a href="http://www.ietf.org/rfc/rfc2822.txt" rel="nofollow"&gt;SMTP&lt;/a&gt; in this regard, so check out how &lt;a href="http://golang.org/pkg/net/smtp/" rel="nofollow"&gt;&lt;code&gt;net/smtp&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/a&gt; is implemented.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;And server-side IMAP implementation differ from client side only in that it most of the time responds to commands, not initiate them, so check out &lt;a href="https://code.google.com/p/go-imap/" rel="nofollow"&gt;existing client implementation&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class="post-text" itemprop="text"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You already copied it form the manual:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;In this example, after sorting, the first array will contain 0, 10, 100, 100. The second array will contain 4, 1, 2, 3. &lt;strong&gt;The entries in the second array corresponding to the identical entries in the first array&lt;/strong&gt; (100 and 100) were sorted as well.&lt;/p&gt;
